<div align="left">
<pre>

CRYING HEART BLUES
Recorded by: Johnny & Jack
Writer: J. Brown

[C] Crying heart blues
I'm crying because I have [G7] lost you
Blues I can't lose, I guess it's too late now to [C] try
I've tried to choose another to love but it's [G7] no use
Crying Heart Blues
There's nothing that's left but to [G7] cry.

I'll [G7] always remember I [C] loved you
My [G7] teardrops won't let me for-[C] get
Each [G7] tear is a wish to be [C] near you
They [D7] started the day that we [G7] met;
A trail of [C] tears will lead you to me if you [G7] want me
And from my tears, my hopeless, my crying heart [G7] flees.

Repeat last verse.

SOURCE:
HITS BY JOHNNY AND JACK
1960 RCA Records LPM-2017

</pre>
